{{Quote|''Star Wars Insider'' attempted to interview Korman in 2003 for the 25th anniversary of the Holiday Special; the phone call with his agent was unintentionally hilarious, as the confused man kept marveling, "Harvey was in ''Star Wars''? Harvey!?"|[[Alex Newborn]]|<ref name="Bad Feeling">{{InsiderCite|106|I Have a Bad Feeling About This!}}</ref>}}
'''Harvey Korman''' portrayed [[Krelman]], [[Gormaanda/Legends|Chef Gormaanda]], and [[Dromboid]] in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. He later played "Jules Cogley" in [[George Lucas]]'s [[1994]] film [[Wikipedia:Radioland Murders|''Radioland Murders'']].

Korman was best known for his work on the popular television variety series ''The Carol Burnett Show'' and his appearances in Mel Brooks films such as ''Blazing Saddles''.

Korman passed away at the age of 81 on May 29, 2008, at UCLA Medical Center.

